# Mini Demo Components

Read `docs/mini_demos.md` for the engineering spec and `docs/mda_director.md` for the creative direction rulebook before writing any demo code.

## Two Systems: MDA and DMC

There are two demo systems sharing the same primitives and principles:

| | MDA (Mini Demo Animation) | DMC (Demo Mini Component) |
|--|---------------------------|--------------------------|
| **Purpose** | Full app window demo for landing page | Focused feature demo for articles |
| **Engine** | `useDemoEngine` (hardcoded `DemoState`) | `useDmcEngine<S, P>` (generic state) |
| **Shell** | `MiniShell` + `DemoShellView` | No shell — custom lightweight orchestrator |
| **Container** | Absolute-positioned inside feature sections | **Fixed-height** (e.g. `h-[280px]`) — NO layout shift |
| **Background** | Parent provides `bg-surface-frost-05` | Parent provides `bg-surface-frost-05` — DMC is transparent |
| **Folder** | `src/site/components/<feature>-demo/` | `src/site/components/<feature>-dmc/` |
| **Types** | `mini-demo/types.ts` | `mini-demo/dmc-types.ts` |

Both must be registered in `src/site/lib/mdaRegistry.ts`.

## Mandatory Workflow

Creating or redesigning an MDA or DMC **must** follow this pipeline in order:

1. **Director** — invoke the `mda-director` skill. Produce a Direction Spec (mood, goal, cast, capabilities, content pool requirements). No code.
2. **Script Writer** — invoke the `mda-scriptwriter` skill. Write `direction.ts` with Direction object (goal, rules, actors, content pool). No components.
3. **Implementation** — build the orchestrator that maps engine state to UI using shared primitives from `mini-demo/`.

Skipping steps is forbidden. If the direction changes, go back to the Director.

## Engine Architecture

### MDA Engine

Demos use the **headless rule-based engine** (`useDemoEngine`). The engine:
- Evaluates rules against abstract `DemoState` each tick
- Emits `Transition` objects (actor + verb + subject + state update)
- Knows nothing about UI, DOM, cursors, or components
- Loops endlessly — when the goal is reached, a new cycle begins from the living state

The **orchestrator** (AppDemo.tsx, GitHubDemo.tsx) is the only layer that maps engine transitions to cursor targets and component props.

### DMC Engine

DMCs use the **generic engine** (`useDmcEngine<S, P>`). Same architecture as MDA engine but:
- Type-parameterized over custom state `S` and pool `P` (no shared `DemoState`)
- Direction includes explicit `initialState` and `resetCycle` function
- Optional `tickDelay` (defaults to 1000ms)

Types: `DmcDirection<S, P>`, `DmcRule<S, P>`, `DmcTransition<S>`, `DmcEngineOutput<S>` from `mini-demo/dmc-types.ts`.

## DMC Container — CRITICAL

DMC containers **must have a stable size**. DMCs render inside article pages and article cards. If the container auto-sizes, content appearing and disappearing causes layout shift that moves article body text.

Use `aspect-square` for a square container that fills the parent width:

```
CORRECT:  className="relative aspect-square"
WRONG:    className="relative"  (auto height — causes layout shift)
```

Use **absolute-positioned crossfade layers** with **percentage-based sizing**:

```tsx
<div className="relative aspect-square">
  <div className={`absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center p-[12%] ... ${showA ? 'opacity-100' : 'opacity-0 pointer-events-none'}`}>
    <div className="w-full max-w-[75%]"><CardComponent /></div>
  </div>
  <div className={`absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center p-[10%] ... ${showB ? 'opacity-100' : 'opacity-0 pointer-events-none'}`}>
    <div className="w-full max-w-[85%]"><ModalComponent /></div>
  </div>
</div>
```

Cards: `max-w-[75%]`, modals: `max-w-[85%]`, padding: `p-[10-12%]`. Never fixed pixel widths — they don't scale.

NEVER conditionally render (`{show && <Component />}`) at the top level of a DMC — use opacity crossfades with pointer-events-none instead.

## DMC Background — CRITICAL

DMC components must NOT set their own background color. The parent container (ArticlePage or ArticleCard) provides `bg-surface-frost-05` to match the landing page feature sections. The DMC should be transparent so the frost background shows through.

```
CORRECT:  className="relative h-[280px]"              (transparent)
WRONG:    className="relative h-[280px] bg-surface-base"  (overrides frost bg)
```

## DMC Organic Timing — CRITICAL

DMCs must feel **organic**. Multiple DMCs visible on the same page must never beat in unison.

The engine has three timing controls:
- `tickDelay` — base delay (default 1000ms)
- `tickJitter` — random ±variance per tick (default 400ms)
- `startDelay` — max random offset before first tick (default 2000ms)

Rules:
- DMCs that share a page (e.g. articles list) MUST use **different `tickDelay`** values (e.g. 1000 vs 1100)
- Default jitter is always applied — never set `tickJitter: 0`
- Use **different actors** for different DMCs — not always "Arvid". Human actions (clicking, inspecting) use human actors; AI analysis (scanning, evaluating) uses Arvid.

## Article Integration

### ArticlePage

The MDA/DMC wrapper in `ArticlePage.tsx` MUST include `bg-surface-frost-05`:

```tsx
<div className="overflow-hidden rounded-card bg-surface-frost-05">
```

### ArticleCard

`ArticleCard` accepts an optional `miniDemoId` prop. When present and the card is `featured` variant, it renders the demo lazily from `MDA_REGISTRY` with `bg-surface-frost-05` container. All callers with article data (ArticlesListPage, LearnMoreSection) MUST pass `miniDemoId={article.mini_demo_id}`.

### Registry

Every MDA and DMC must be registered in `mdaRegistry.ts` with a descriptive label (shown in CMS admin dropdown).

## RequirementCard — Shared Base

`app-demo/RequirementCard.tsx` is the **canonical requirement card for all demos** (MDA and DMC). It renders:
- Header: short ID (mono) + ellipsis menu icon
- Title
- Chips row: completeness % (solid bg) + optional status chip + optional impl status chip
- Footer: owner + date + indicator dots

The `Requirement` type has optional `status` and `implStatus` fields. Cards gracefully omit chips for absent fields. When a DMC needs cursor targeting on the impl chip, pass `implChipTarget` prop.

## Architecture (enforced)

1. MDAs live in `src/site/components/<feature>-demo/`, DMCs in `<feature>-dmc/`, both with barrel `index.ts`.
2. Shared primitives live in `src/site/components/mini-demo/` — one component per file.
3. Demo sub-components must compose primitives with zero `className` or `style` attributes on the primitives.
4. Sub-components get their own files, named for their role in the feature narrative.
5. The orchestrator is a thin wiring layer: derives display state from engine state, passes as props.
6. Pass a container `ref` to the engine for viewport-aware playback.

## Animation Timing

- Demos must feel **slow, ambient, and continuous**.
- Demos **loop seamlessly** — the viewer must never perceive a restart point.
- MDA cycles: 20-30 seconds (18s hard minimum). DMC cycles: 14-20 seconds.
- CSS transitions: `duration-300` (micro), `duration-500` (standard), `duration-700` (major + fade-outs). No other values.

## Visual Fidelity

- All colors, weights, radii, shadows, and borders from `src/styles/theme.css` tokens.
- Use shared primitives instead of building UI from scratch.
- Demo-scale text: `text-[9px]` titles, `text-[8px]` body/headers, `text-[7px]` metadata, `text-[6px]` micro labels.
- Radius: `rounded-standard` for cards, `rounded-micro` for chips/badges, `rounded-card` for outer containers.
- No placeholder content — all text must be realistic and meaningful.

## MiniShell Positioning — CRITICAL (MDA only)

`MiniShell` uses a **two-div structure** to avoid a CSS position conflict. See `docs/mini_demos.md` § "MiniShell Positioning" for the full explanation.

- **NEVER** add `position: relative` to MiniShell's outer div
- **NEVER** remove the inner `relative` wrapper div

DMCs do not use MiniShell, so this constraint does not apply to them.

## Forbidden

- DMC container without stable size — use `aspect-square` (auto-sizing causes layout shift in articles)
- DMC container with its own background color (must be transparent — parent provides frost bg)
- ArticlePage or ArticleCard MDA wrapper without `bg-surface-frost-05`
- ArticleCard callers not passing `miniDemoId` when article data is available
- Adding `relative`, `fixed`, or `sticky` to MiniShell's outer div (MDA only)
- Writing demo code without a Director's Treatment and a reviewed script
- Generic component names (`DemoSidebar`, `DemoCard`, `DemoPanel`)
- `className` or `style` attributes on shared primitives in demo sub-components
- Hardcoded colors, font weights, or border radii
- Lorem ipsum or meaningless placeholder text
- Duration values other than `duration-300`, `duration-500`, `duration-700`
- Conditional rendering (`{show && <Component />}`) at the top level of a DMC — use opacity crossfades
- Setting `tickJitter: 0` (removes organic feel, causes lockstep with other DMCs)
- Using "Arvid" as actor for human actions (clicking, inspecting) — use a human name
- Multiple DMCs with identical `tickDelay` (they'll sync up on the same page)
- Fixed pixel widths on DMC cards/modals (`max-w-[220px]`) — use percentage-based `max-w-[75%]` / `max-w-[85%]`
- Fixed pixel padding on DMC layers (`p-6`) — use percentage `p-[10%]` / `p-[12%]`
